FBIS4-18832 "drweu069_i_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-069 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 FRANCE Military Intervention in Rwanda Ruled Out Military Intervention in Rwanda Ruled Out LD0804154194 Paris Radio France International in French 1500 GMT 8 Apr 94 LD0804154194 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Excerpts] [passage omitted] France has ruled out any further military intervention in Rwanda such as its intervention between October 1990 to December 1993. [passage omitted]. The French cooperation minister has moreover said that more than 50 Rwandan ministers and high-ranking civil servants and their families have been taking refuge in the French Embassy in Kigali since yesterday evening, where they are now under the protection of a unit of 30 French soldiers who are still in Rwanda.
